The paper deals with graph theoretic problems and their complexity with respect to various graph parameters such as clique-width, split-width, and modular-width. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Among these categories, cs.DS and cs.CC are the most likely as they are directly related to the main focus of the paper.
